8:
Please open your textbooks to page
39. Last time—
13: And that outfit. It suits him perfectly...
19:
Heh. Mr. Fancypants' good looks are
a bit of a classroom disruption, eh?
23:
And that's how you solve the
question. Do you understand?
26:
Y-yes! You explained it perfectly,
Professor!
28:
Also, um... Th-that new suit, it looks
great on you!
31:
...Thank you. I had it tailored for the
Academy's holiday party, so I'm
happy to hear that.
34:
...Also, Professor... If you don't have
any other plans for the holidays—
36:
I'm sorry, but I'm afraid I'll be
preoccupied with a prior
commitment.
42:
A prior commitment, huh? Aren't you
the social butterfly.
47:
You've got the wrong impression. I'll
be helping one of the professor's
grandchildren with their elementary
studies.
51:
Oh, that professor from the research
team? The one helping out with
cursebreaking?
58:
Many were frozen in ice by my
brother after he stole my Oculus.
61:
I had no choice but to freeze my
brother as well, but this man has
been helping me find a way to save
them all.
64:
...Thanks to him, there is hope in
saving everyone.
72:
However, it will be difficult to procure
the necessary materials for
cursebreaking. The Academy made
a formal request—
76:
Oh, there you are, Reylas. I was
wondering where you were, 
but I wasn't expecting to see Alk 
and Nimbus with you.
80:
Well, if it isn't the Grand Witch
herself. You two on the same
research team?
84:
He and I are working together to
break the curse that's trapped
others in time. We're kindred spirits,
he and I!
88:
...It's thanks to her that I've been
fighting against reality itself on a
daily basis. My Oculus even
malfunctioned...
96:
Well enough. I suppose I'm just
someone who struggles to think
outside the box.
99:
At any rate, did you need me for
something?
104:
The Professor said the preparations
for the party are finished, but
wanted to know how the
material-gathering for the
cursebreaking was coming along.
108:
I was just about to discuss that with
Alk, actually.
111:
Oh? Well, as long as things are
coming along. The demonstration's
in three days, you know!
115:
Three days? Shouldn't be a problem,
I think we could have everything
gathered by tomorrow.
120:
Indeed, we've nothing to worry
about. As for the other tasks to take
care of...
124:
...My apologies, allow me to retract
my previous statement. There may
be more to worry about than I
thought.
126:
I'll accompany you with gathering
the materials since I have another
task that needs doing in the same
area. If you could also help me with
another task...
135:
Glad somebody's relying on others
for once.
142:
Postpone the party. We're running
ourselves ragged just to gather
materials for ice sculptures?
146: Yeah, this is a little much. I'm wiped.
151:
What can I say... It seems that I've
been roped into making the
holidays a little more festive.
154:
Your hard work is very much
appreciated.
161:
Now that you mention it, though,
you've really figured out how to do a
lot with that eye of yours. Even ice
sculpting!
164:
...Cipher pushed me into it on a
whim.
167:
However, using magic without
applying theory or reason is surely
linked to considerable skill.
170: Besides, you'll teach me, won't you?
173:
This eye is good for far more than
harming others.
177:
You're brother's going to be pretty
surprised, I bet.
182:
Haha, I'm sure he will be. It wouldn't
be so bad for me to regain some
dignity as the older brother...
207:
You've really been getting a lot of
attention from people, haven't you?
Mr. Dragon-Slaying Professor.
211:
Haha, I suppose I have been. So
much so that I struggle to even think
about it.
214: The fame's getting to your head?
217:
I'm just remembering how things
were back home. I'm not used to
being respected in any genuine
sense, and it makes me feel ill at
ease.
222:
Haha. If anything, I think you could
stand to cut loose and brag a little.
226:
I don't want you drinking yourself
into a stupor all alone, going on
about not dragging others into your
problems.
229:
Oh... Well, you needn't worry about
that.
231:
Both in Starview Village and the
Academy, people very rarely let me
go out alone.
236:
By the way, I'm quite fond of
Palpebra's sake, but what about you?
240:
Wow. Didn't think you'd be the
educator who'd play hooky.
244:
I'm not skipping anything, this is a
matter of prioritization. And I'm in
the mood for going out drinking with
a friend.
247:
All right, then. You know a place with
good sake?
251:
I do indeed. Allow me to lead the
way.
